9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1200, L.D. 1789, “An Act to Amend the
10 Education and Experience Requirements and Add Reciprocity Privileges in the Certified
11 Public Accountancy Licensure Laws”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Amend the Education Requirements in the Certified Public Accountant
14 Licensure Laws'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 32 MRSA §12228, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2011, c. 478, §1, is further
18 amended to read:
19 3. Education requirement requirements. The education requirement for a license
20 is and the education requirement to take the examination are as follows:
21 B. At least 150 semester hours of education, including a minimum 4-year
22 baccalaureate or higher degree conferred by a college or university acceptable to the
23 board, the total educational program to include basic courses in accounting and
24 auditing determined to be appropriate under board rules, is required for licensure.
25 Rules adopted by the board pursuant to this paragraph are routine technical rules as
26 defined in Title 5, chapter 375, subchapter 2‑A; and
27 C. An examination applicant who has successfully completed at least 120 semester
28 hours of education, including the basic courses in accounting and auditing required by
29 paragraph B, and who expects to complete a minimum 4-year baccalaureate or higher
30 degree required in paragraph B within 120 days following the examination is eligible
31 to take the examination. Grades may not be released, nor may credit for the
32 examination or any part of the examination be given to the applicant unless the degree
33 required in paragraph B is completed within 120 days following the examination or
34 within such time as the board in its sole discretion may determine.'
